DataElement.preferredName: Day Two Post Injection Procedure Administered Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date that occurred on day 2 after an injection of medication or vaccine was given.

Concepts.definition: The time for Earth to make a complete rotation on its axis; ordinarily divided into twenty-four hours, equal to 86 400 seconds. This also refers to a specific day.
A natural number greater than 1 and less than 3 and the quantity that it denotes: the sum of one and one.
Happening at a time subsequent to a reference time; later in time or order.
Administration of a drug into a location within the body; this can be achieved either through an established access or via a needle.
The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).
